  <item>
    <title>*Keybindings* in Amber's new IDE</title>
    <link>http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/helios-keybindings.html#orgheadline1</link>
    <author>nicolas@petton.fr (Nicolas Petton)</author>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/helios-keybindings.html#orgheadline1</guid>
    <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jan 2014 13:10:00 +0100</pubDate>

    <description><![CDATA[<div class="pubdate">
    January 13, 2014
    </div>

    <p>
    Amber's new IDE, fondly named Helios, has been built with keyboard
    power users in mind from the beginning. It evolved quite a bit over
    time, and keyboard shortcuts as well as their UI are no exception.
    </p>

    <p>
    Last week we improved the Keybinding helper UI in helios, making it
    more prominent and accessible. The previous version was greatly
    inspired by Emacs' minibuffer, and while I'm an Emacs user, I think
    this iteration makes it a lot more accessible.
    </p>

    <p>
    Here's a short video demonstrating the new user interface.
    </p>

